vmware_nsxlib/v3/policy/core_defs.py.message:
NSX dictates this. If you try patching something like:
{
  "resource_type": "Group",
  "id": "test-group",
  "expression":
    [{"expressions": [
        {"key": "Tag", "member_type": "LogicalPort", "operator": "EQUALS", "resource_type": "Condition", "value": "tag1|value1"},
        {"conjunction_operator": "OR", "resource_type": "ConjunctionOperator"},
        {"key": "Tag", "member_type": "LogicalPort", "operator": "EQUALS", "resource_type": "Condition", "value": "tag2|value2"}
      ],
      "resource_type": "NestedExpression"}
    ]
}
You will get this following error msg:
{
  "httpStatus": "BAD_REQUEST",
  "error_code": 500112,
  "module_name": "Policy",
  "error_message": "Nested expression should have only Condition nodes. Only AND operator is supported in a nested expression."
}

